  "title": "Technical Lead - Permanent, Startup",
  "description": "<ul><li>Permanent role</li><li>Part of a fast-growing team and exposure with emerging technology products</li></ul><h2>About Our Client</h2><p>This firm is a well-established organisation operating within the Technology & Telecoms industry. They are known for their impactful contributions and innovative solutions, supporting the growth and development of their sector.</p><h2>Job Description</h2><ul><li><strong>Lead the design, development, and implementation</strong> of technical projects within the Technology department.</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to deliver scalable and efficient solutions.</li><li><strong>Mentor and guide junior</strong> engineers to foster professional growth within the team.</li><li>Conduct code reviews to maintain high-quality standards across projects.</li><li><strong>Manage project timelines and deliverables</strong> effectively, ensuring successful completion.</li><li>Stay updated on emerging technologies and recommend their adoption where appropriate.</li></ul><h2>The Successful Applicant</h2><p>A successful Senior/Lead Engineer should have:</p><ul><li>Strong <strong>technical expertise in full stack development</strong> with relevant programming languages and frameworks</li><li>Proven ability to <strong>lead and manage engineering teams</strong> effectively</li><li>Experience in delivering large-scale projects within the Technology industry</li><li>Excellent problem-solving skills and a proactive approach to challenges</li><li>A collaborative mindset with strong communication skills to work across teams</li></ul><h2>What's on Offer</h2><ul><li>Competitive annual salary package</li><li>Opportunity to work on impactful projects within the Technology & Telecoms industry.</li><li>Collaborative work environment based in Singapore.</li></ul><p><br /><br />If you are a driven Senior/Lead Engineer ready to make a significant impact, apply now to join this exciting opportunity in Singapore.</p><p>Contact</p><p>Cheryl Ang (Lic No: R2091316/ EA no: 18C9065)</p><p>Quote job ref</p><p>JN-112025-6875669</p><p>Phone number</p><p>+65 6416 9884</p>",
